post_text:
We are proud to announce the second year of our WOLCS Scholarship Program. This program will provide financial assistance to support alumni students (graduates of WOLCS) pursuing college and/or career training programs. We realize that finances are often a barrier to completing academic programs; therefore, we hope students who are in financial need will be encouraged to apply.

Scholarships are for $2500 each. Please click application linked to this post.

The application submission period will close March 27, 2020, at 4:00 PM. #WOLCSphila

post_text:
WOLCS will open on a 2 hour delay tomorrow, Tuesday, February 12th. The delayed opening means that school will begin for students at 10:00am. Students will be admitted into the building beginning at 9:45am. Please note that breakfast will not be served to students tomorrow.

Also, students who take the school bus should arrive to the bus stop two hours after their usual pick up time. Ms Zeigler will notify you via DOJO of any bus issues that gets communicated to from Durham.

We will keep you informed of any updates. Please be safe and have a wonderful night!

Also, students who take the school bus should arrive to the bus stop two hours after their usual pick up time. Ms Zeigler will notify you via DOJO of any bus issues that gets communicated to from Durham.

We will keep you informed of any updates. Please be safe and have a wonderful night!

Hi Parents or Guardians:

Based on a parent survey from the last FBI meeting, 42.9% of parents indicated that they were interested in a financial workshop. So, we need your help to determine the topic for the first meeting on Wedneday, October 24, 2018 at 6p.m. Please take 60 seconds to answer the questionnaire. Deadline for questionnaire is Wednesday, October 17th by 4:30 p.m.

This is also a opportunity for you tell us other topics you would like to see covered by administrators, deans, or outside professional presenters.

Thank you for your input

post_text: Week 6 – Breakfast is the most important meal of the day! Snap a picture of 3/5 healthy food groups for breakfast. The 5 food groups are whole grains, fruits, veggies, low fat milk and lean protein. Some common lean protein options for breakfast are eggs, turkey bacon or turkey sausage, low fat cheese, and low fat yogurt. Here is a great example of what a 3/5 healthy breakfast plate looks like! Only one picture should be emailed. Remember, your submission is due no later than Sunday August 19th. Good Luck!

Week 1 of the WOLCS Summer Wellness Challenge

Drink 6-8 cups of water per day. You can start gradually and work up to 6-8 cups by the end of the week! Life Hack – one normal sized plastic water bottle = 2 cups! However, reusable water bottles are always encouraged. Simply email a picture of you drinking water OR an empty water bottle in your hand. You do not have to be in the picture for the submission to count! Since this is the first week, this challenge is based on the honors system. Only one picture should be emailed but try to do this as many days out of the week as possible! Remember, your submission is due no later than Sunday July 15th. Good Luck!

post_text:
In honor of our 20th Anniversary, WOLCS will construct a WOLCS Community Champions Wall in the atrium of our school to thank all those that have financially supported our school over the years and made it a pillar in the West Oak Lane community. While many of the Champions displayed on the wall will be local businesses, executives and community leaders, we know that YOU are the real WOLCS Champions! Thus, we are launching a special WOLCS Community Champions Campaign to show that we are building community with LOVE.

You can make a donation of $20 or more to the WOLCS School Fund to have your name, family name or business displayed on the wall.

post_text: Last Night WOLCS hosted the Wild About Reading. It is the summer reading initiative for students in grades K-2. With funding support from Mike Jones of PK Financial Group each student in grades K-2 will receive 3-4 books to take home for the summer and have the opportunity to swap out books throughout the summer. The kick-off event held on 6/6 included snacks, crafts, and games in addition to students receiving a backpack and having the opportunity to choose their summer reading books. 83 students turned out for the event and it was a huge success! Thank you PK Financial Group for your support!!

post_text:
Due to the forecasted inclement weather, West Oak Lane Charter School will be closed tomorrow, Tuesday, March 14, 2017.

All students have been provided with grade level assignments to be completed while at home. You may also access these assignments on our Home Page by clicking the link ‘SNOW DAY Assignments.”

Stay tuned for updated information on our website and all news channels.

Please be safe!
